Set up a multibuild environment as described in BUILDING_MULTITARGET_FULL.

Build cpp-ethereum:
    Clone the main repo
    $ git clone https://github.com/ethereum/cpp-ethereum
    $ cd cpp-ethereum

    Update the cmake files
    $ git remote add codeshark https://github.com/CodeShark/cpp-ethereum
    $ git fetch codeshark
    $ git checkout codeshark/cmake_multitarget \
        CMakeLists.txt \
        libethereum/CMakeLists.txt \
        test/CMakeLists.txt \
        eth/CMakeLists.txt \
        alethzero/CMakeLists.txt \
        windows/qt_plugin_import.cpp
    $ cd ..

    $ mkdir cpp-ethereum-build
    $ cd cpp-ethereum-build
    $ cmake ../cpp-ethereum -DTARGET_PLATFORM=<target>
        (<target> can be either linux or w64)
    $ make
    $ cd ..
